(22256, 'drug_class', 'N/A', 'major', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS Nephrotoxic Drugs and Diuretics: May increase the risk of renal failure; avoid concomitant use. (7.1, 7.2) Neurotoxic Drugs: May potentiate CNS toxicity of mannitol; avoid concomitant use. (7.3) Drugs Affected by Electrolyte Imbalances: May result in cardiac adverse reactions; monitor serum electrolytes and discontinue Mannitol Injection if cardiac status worsens. (7.4) Renally Eliminated Agents: Concomitant use may decrease the effectiveness of agents that undergo significant renal elimination. However, concomitant use of mannitol and lithium may increase risk of lithium toxicity. If concomitant use is necessary, frequently monitor lithium concentrations and for signs of toxicity. (7.5) 7.1 Nephrotoxic Drugs Concomitant administration of nephrotoxic drugs (e.g., aminog', 'DailyMed'),
